<p>I would like to bind a listview with nested lists and I'm having some problems doing it more particularly to have them for the headers AND the item.</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/abCBH.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/abCBH.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>I have a list of CDs. The CD class has a unique album ID and list of songs. I want the Headers to be the album ID and the content of the list the songs name.</p>  <p>I never found a solution that explains how to create headers according to the list without specifying them. Most of the time, people just create Header as a string, not a binding element retrieved from the list.</p>  <p><strong>I DO NOT want to do something like it:</strong></p>  <pre><code>  &lt;ListView Grid.Row="1"           HorizontalAlignment="Stretch"           ItemsSource='{Binding CDs}'&gt;     &lt;ListView.View&gt;       &lt;GridView&gt;         &lt;GridViewColumn Header="Album 1"                       DisplayMemberBinding="{Binding Path=Songs}"                       Width="Auto" /&gt;         &lt;GridViewColumn Header="Album 2"                       DisplayMemberBinding="{Binding Path=Songs}"                       Width="Auto" /&gt;       &lt;/GridView&gt;     &lt;/ListView.View&gt;   &lt;/ListView&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I want to create the headers in a loop as I have no ideas how much albums have my CDs list. I'm ok with code behind solution even if in XAML will be prefered.</p>  <p><strong>I succeed</strong> to display what I wanted BUT the headers are not linked to the items (meaning that resizing an header will have no impact on its items...).</p>  <pre><code>&lt;ListView x:Name="CDsListView" ItemsSource="{Binding CDs}""&gt;     &lt;ListView.View&gt;     &lt;GridView AllowsColumnReorder="False"&gt;             &lt;GridView.ColumnHeaderTemplate&gt;             &lt;DataTemplate DataType="{x:Type viewmodel:ViewModel+CD}"&gt;                 &lt;StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal"&gt;                     &lt;TextBlock x:Name="AlbumTitle" Text="{Binding Path=AlbumID}"/&gt;                     &lt;Rectangle x:Name="AlbumImage" Fill="{Binding Path=AlbumImage}" Width="30" Height="20"/&gt;                 &lt;/StackPanel&gt;             &lt;/DataTemplate&gt;         &lt;/GridView.ColumnHeaderTemplate&gt;     &lt;/GridView&gt;     &lt;ListBox.ItemTemplate&gt;         &lt;DataTemplate&gt;              &lt;local:SongControl/&gt;         &lt;/DataTemplate&gt;     &lt;/ListBox.ItemTemplate&gt; &lt;/ListView&gt; </code></pre>  <p>And adding the column headers in code behind:</p>  <pre><code>GridView gridView = CDsListView.View as GridView; gridView.Columns.Clear();  foreach (ViewModel.CD cdContext in ViewModel.CDs) {     GridViewColumn column = new GridViewColumn();     column.Header = cdContext;     gridView.Columns.Add(column); } </code></pre>  <p>What am I doing wrong ?</p>  <p>Thank you</p>